Description/specs from Jackson Kayak's website follows: . . ."Mini Tripper" At 9 feet long this kayak has been designed specifically for kids in every way. This wont just be just an adult boat sized down for kids The Mini Tripper has design features that allow kids to paddle with the confidence required to enjoy all that paddling offers. Its design provides for quite an impressive hull speed and keeps up well with the adult versions while still providing amazing stability. This boat, just like the adult versions, is ultra comfortable, tracks like its on a rail and is very stable. It is light enough for most kids to handle carting it on their own, paddles straight... Length: 109.88″ Width: 23″ Weight: 27 lbs Carrying Capacity: 40 -- 140 lbs 2010 MSRP: $499 I may be out of red ones, but have yellow, and maybe green. Will take $250 for one boat alone, or $450 for 2 together, no paddles or lifejackets, or $300 each with choice.  (Before Christmas,) I have 1 or two with some oil canning, or a missing foot peg that I can let go for less.
